FBIS4-13645 "drnes078dd_94002" FBIS-NES-94-078 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 Palestinian Affairs 'Arafat To Meet With Hamas Leaders in Jordan 'Arafat To Meet With Hamas Leaders in Jordan NC2204092094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0905 GMT 22 Apr 94 NC2204092094 Cairo MENA Arabic BFN [Excerpt] Abu Dhabi, 22 Apr (MENA)-- The newspaper AL-ITTIHAD of Abu Dhabi today reports that Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat will pay an urgent visit to Jordan next week to meet for the first time with the leaders of "Hamas" [Islamic Resistance Movement], which recently offered a truce with Israel in return for the latter's withdrawal from the occupied territories and its dismantling of settlements. The paper welcomes the visit, noting that it is the first time 'Arafat has met with Hamas leaders, particularly Muhammad Nazzal and Ibrahim Ghawshah, to prepare for full reconciliation between the PLO and the Movement. [passage omitted]
